{
	"nodes":[
		{"id":"eda-main","type":"text","text":"## ⚡ EDA / Electrodermal Activity (GSR)\n\nThe most direct sympathetic nervous system signal available on-wrist. Captures arousal that HRV alone misses.\n\n**Bidirectional Pattern (Critical for App):**\n- **Chronic LOW tonic EDA** → depression, suicidal ideation, emotional blunting\n- **Acute HIGH phasic spikes** → transition from ideation to self-harm action\n- **Slow habituation** to auditory tones = volitional factor in IMV model\n\n**Device Availability:**\n- Samsung GW8: Continuous EDA (1 Hz)\n- Samsung GW6/7: Spot-check EDA via BioActive sensor\n- Pixel Watch 2/3: cEDA all-day tracking\n- Fitbit Charge 5/6: 90-sec spot-check only","x":-400,"y":-380,"width":400,"height":580},
		{"id":"eda-paper-2","type":"link","url":"https://www.nature.com/articles/s44220-025-00520-5","x":50,"y":280,"width":400,"height":400},
		{"id":"hrv-paper-1","type":"link","url":"https://www.frontiersin.org/journals/psychiatry/articles/10.3389/fpsyt.2021.652340","x":500,"y":350,"width":400,"height":400},
		{"id":"hrv-paper-2","type":"link","url":"https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/27124209/","x":950,"y":50,"width":400,"height":400},
		{"id":"hrv-paper-3","type":"link","url":"https://www.sciencedirect.com/science/article/abs/pii/S0301051118300759","x":950,"y":500,"width":400,"height":400},
		{"id":"sleep-main","type":"text","text":"## 😴 Sleep as Proximal Predictor\n\nSleep disturbance is not just a correlate — it's a **temporal precursor** to next-day suicidal ideation.\n\n**Key Predictive Features (Accelerometer-Derived):**\n\n1. **Sleep Onset Time Variance** (7-day SD)\n   - High variability predicts suicidal symptoms at 7 & 21 days\n   - More predictive than total duration alone\n\n2. **Sleep Efficiency** (% time in bed actually asleep)\n   - Psychiatric inpatients with sleep disturbance → significantly more active suicidal ideation next day\n\n3. **Nightmares / Restlessness**\n   - Unidirectional relationship: nightmares predict post-sleep self-harming thoughts\n   - Independent of depressive symptoms and negative affect\n\n4. **Sleep Stage Architecture**\n   - REM, Deep, Light proportions\n   - Galaxy Watch / Pixel Watch provide sleep staging via accelerometer + HR","x":-400,"y":1060,"width":400,"height":670},
		{"id":"sleep-paper-1","type":"link","url":"https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pmc/articles/PMC8793208/","x":-400,"y":1820,"width":400,"height":400},
		{"id":"sleep-paper-2","type":"link","url":"https://pmc.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/articles/PMC12169096/","x":50,"y":1550,"width":400,"height":400},
		{"id":"fusion-paper-1","type":"link","url":"https://www.psychiatryinvestigation.org/journal/view.php?doi=10.30773/pi.2024.0257","x":500,"y":1820,"width":400,"height":400},
		{"id":"fusion-bipolar","type":"link","url":"https://pmc.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/articles/PMC12169096/","x":950,"y":2050,"width":400,"height":400},
		{"id":"clinical-main","type":"text","text":"## 🏥 Clinical Validation & Feasibility\n\n**Harvard / Franciscan Hospital Study (Kleiman et al. 2019):**\n- Population: Suicidal adolescent inpatients (ages 12–19)\n- Includes: severe suicidal ideation, suicide attempts, NSSI\n- **Finding: Wearable monitoring is feasible and acceptable**\n- Target population WILL wear wrist sensors and provide valid data\n- This is crucial proof-of-concept for real-world deployment\n\n**Anonymous Online CBT Trial (NCT06465589):**\n- 452 participants, anonymous online CBT for social anxiety\n- Anonymous tools process NO personal data → removes privacy barrier\n- Users may have **preference** for anonymous versions\n- Anonymity reduces stigma-related dropout\n\n**Digital Meta-Analysis (Nature npj Digital Medicine):**\n- Anxiety reduction: SMD = -0.38 (significant)\n- Depression reduction: SMD = -0.35 (significant)\n- Psychological distress: SMD = -0.40 (significant)\n- Most effective: mHealth, telehealth, social media-based\n- Both <8 weeks and ≥8 weeks effective","x":-900,"y":860,"width":420,"height":870},
		{"id":"clinical-paper-1","type":"link","url":"https://mhealth.jmir.org/2019/9/e13725","x":-900,"y":1820,"width":400,"height":400},
		{"id":"clinical-paper-3","type":"link","url":"https://www.nature.com/articles/s41746-025-02266-x","x":-1350,"y":2050,"width":400,"height":400},
		{"id":"eda-bidirectional","type":"text","text":"### 🔄 The Bidirectional EDA Paradox\n\n| State | EDA Pattern | Clinical Meaning |\n|-------|-------------|------------------|\n| **Suicidal Ideation** | Hypoactive (low tonic) | Emotional numbing, depression |\n| **Self-Harm Action** | Hyperactive (phasic spikes) | Arousal driving enactment |\n| **Non-Suicidal Self-Injury** | Heightened EDA, slower habituation | Distinguishable from ideation-only |\n\n**App Requirement:** Track BOTH baseline tonic level AND phasic spike frequency. A model watching only one direction will misclassify.\n\n*Within the IMV model, heightened EDA arousal is a volitional factor underpinning the transition from thought to action.*","x":-1400,"y":680,"width":400,"height":550},
		{"id":"clinical-paper-2","type":"link","url":"https://pmc.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/articles/PMC12631092/","x":-1640,"y":1440,"width":400,"height":400},
		{"id":"metrics-table","type":"text","text":"## 📊 Key Metrics Summary Table\n\n| Biomarker | Wearable Source | Suicide Risk Signal | Accuracy / Caveat | Priority |\n|-----------|-----------------|---------------------|-------------------|----------|\n| **EDA Tonic (low)** | Samsung GW8, Pixel Watch | Depression, ideation, blunting | Direct sympathetic marker | 🔴 HIGH |\n| **EDA Phasic (spikes)** | Samsung GW8, Pixel Watch | Transition to action (IMV model) | Confounded by exercise, heat | 🔴 HIGH |\n| **Sleep RMSSD** | All PPG watches | Vagal tone, emotion regulation | Best during sleep; noisy awake | 🔴 HIGH |\n| **HRV Reactivity** | All PPG watches | Inability to recover from stress | Requires stress event detection | 🟡 MEDIUM |\n| **Sleep Onset Variance** | Accelerometer | Next-day ideation predictor | 7-day rolling SD > 90 min | 🔴 HIGH |\n| **Sleep Efficiency** | Accelerometer + HR | Proximal next-day risk | Validated in psychiatric inpatients | 🔴 HIGH |\n| **Nightmares/Restlessness** | Accelerometer | Post-sleep self-harm thoughts | Proxy via movement + HR during sleep | 🟡 MEDIUM |\n| **Skin Temperature** | Pixel Watch, GW7/8 | Peripheral vasoconstriction, circadian | Ambient temp confounder | 🟢 LOW |\n| **Resting HR** | All PPG watches | Elevated in chronic stress | Non-specific; use as secondary | 🟢 LOW |\n| **SpO2** | All modern watches | Sleep apnea, respiratory | Medical mode flag only | 🟢 LOW |","x":-1260,"y":2540,"width":720,"height":860},
		{"id":"fusion-architecture","type":"text","text":"### 🏗️ Fusion Architecture Layers\n\n**Layer 1 — Signal Quality Gate:**\n- Discard awake-time HRV if motion artifact detected (accelerometer threshold)\n- Use sleep-time HRV as gold-standard baseline\n- EDA valid only if skin contact confirmed (impedance check)\n\n**Layer 2 — Unimodal Feature Extraction:**\n| Modality | Features | Window |\n|----------|----------|--------|\n| EDA | Tonic mean, Phasic peak count, Habituation slope | 24h |\n| HRV | Sleep RMSSD, Reactivity Δ, Recovery tau | 7-day rolling |\n| Sleep | Onset variance, Efficiency, Nightmare proxy (restlessness) | 7-day rolling |\n| Skin Temp | Nadir time, Amplitude, Peripheral vasoconstriction index | 24h |\n| HR | Resting HR, HR surge frequency | 24h |\n\n**Layer 3 — Cross-Modal Attention:**\n- Transformer or LSTM with cross-attention between sensor streams\n- Temporal alignment: all features normalized to same time grid\n\n**Layer 4 — Risk Stratification:**\n- Output: Probability of suicide-related event within 7-day window\n- Threshold adjustable based on clinical setting (inpatient vs. outpatient)","x":320,"y":2380,"width":450,"height":880},
		{"id":"samsung-developer","type":"link","url":"https://developer.samsung.com/health/sensor/guide/data-specifications.html","x":-2320,"y":-1420,"width":1140,"height":940},
		{"id":"sensor-hub","type":"text","text":"## 📡 Consumer Wearable Sensor Capabilities\n\n**Samsung Galaxy Watch 6/7/8:**\n- PPG (optical HR) + ECG + BIA\n- **Accelerometer** (25 Hz) — activity, sleep staging, fall detection\n- **EDA** (1 Hz) — *Galaxy Watch 8+ continuous; GW6/7 spot-check*\n- **Temperature** sensor — skin temp, circadian tracking\n- **Gyroscope, Barometer, Light**\n- SpO2, Sleep apnea detection\n\n**Google Pixel Watch 2/3 / Fitbit Sense 2:**\n- **cEDA** (continuous electrodermal activity)\n- **HRV + HR** via PPG\n- **Skin Temperature** — peripheral vasoconstriction\n- **Accelerometer** — sleep, activity, restlessness\n- Body Response alerts (multi-signal ML)\n\n*Key insight: EDA + HRV + Sleep + Skin Temp = 4-signal stack for stress/arousal detection*","x":-940,"y":-760,"width":420,"height":640},
		{"id":"sensor-paper-google","type":"link","url":"https://research.google/blog/what-does-electrodermal-sensing-reveal-insights-from-the-pixel-watch-fitbit-sense-2/","x":-1620,"y":120,"width":400,"height":400},
		{"id":"eda-paper-1","type":"link","url":"https://bmcpsychiatry.biomedcentral.com/articles/10.1186/s12888-017-1551-4","x":-890,"y":200,"width":400,"height":400},
		{"id":"hrv-samsung-accuracy","type":"link","url":"https://pmc.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/articles/PMC9731465/","x":50,"y":760,"width":400,"height":400},
		{"id":"fusion-main","type":"text","text":"## 🧮 Multi-Modal Mathematical Fusion Model\n\n**Core Principle:** Physiological data from wearables alone does NOT independently predict suicide risk — but shows strong potential when correlated with daily mood/symptom data. Multi-modal fusion is necessary.\n\n**Proposed Risk Score Equation:**\n\n```\nR_score = w_c · x_c + w_b · x_b + w_s · x_s\n```\n\nWhere:\n- **x_c** = Clinical inputs (PHQ-9, GAD-7, prior attempts, diagnoses)\n- **x_b** = Behavioral inputs (app engagement, social media sentiment, GPS mobility patterns)\n- **x_s** = Sensor inputs (EDA, HRV, Sleep, Skin Temp, HR)\n- **w_c, w_b, w_s** = dynamically adjusted weights via SHAP values\n\n**Galaxy Watch Active2 ML Study:**\n- Physiological data alone: insufficient prediction\n- Physiological + mood symptom correlation: strong potential\n- Confirms **fusion is mandatory, not optional**","x":560,"y":840,"width":450,"height":710},
		{"id":"fusion-paper-2","type":"link","url":"https://repository.satbayev.university/api/files/ff7zp4hgeci7mfw0tcmu2euqq.pdf","x":1000,"y":1530,"width":400,"height":400},
		{"id":"hrv-reactivity","type":"text","text":"### 📉 HRV Reactivity > Resting Baseline\n\n**Don't just watch resting HRV — watch the DROP:**\n\n1. **Baseline** (sleep-derived): Personal 7-14 day RMSSD average\n2. **Stress Reactivity**: ΔRMSSD during detected stress events (EDA spike + HR rise)\n3. **Recovery Rate**: How fast RMSSD returns to baseline post-stressor\n\n**Suicide attempters show:**\n- Lower cumulative HF-HRV during stress tests\n- Greater anger increase correlated with reduced HF-HRV\n- Reduced vagal emotion regulation capacity\n\n**Algorithm implication:** A user whose HRV drops sharply AND fails to recover within 30-60 min warrants elevated risk scoring.","x":940,"y":-710,"width":400,"height":570},
		{"id":"sleep-stanford","type":"text","text":"### 🎓 Stanford Sleep-Irregularity Finding\n\n**Study Design:** Wrist accelerometer for 1 week\n\n**Finding:** Participants with high variability in sleep onset/wake times were more likely to experience suicidal symptoms at 7 and 21 days later.\n\n**Critical Feature for Algorithm:**\n- Compute **sleep onset time standard deviation** over rolling 7-day window\n- Flag when SD > 90 minutes (threshold from literature)\n- Combine with next-day mood check-in to validate\n\n*This is a passive, time-series feature that requires no user input — ideal for early warning.*","x":-150,"y":2290,"width":400,"height":500},
		{"id":"fp-main","type":"text","text":"## 🎯 False Positive Reduction Strategies\n\n**The #1 barrier to clinical deployment:** Alert fatigue from excessive false positives. Providers reject tools that cry wolf.\n\n**1. Stability Threshold (Temporal Consistency)**\n- Require risk elevation to persist across **multiple consecutive days**\n- ROC curve over 50 threshold values shows trade-off between TPR and FPR\n- Higher stability threshold → lower FPR, slightly lower TPR\n\n**2. Personal Baseline Calibration (14-30 days)**\n- Each user builds their own physiological baseline\n- Anomaly detection relative to personal norm, not population average\n- Accounts for fitness level, age, medication, chronotype\n\n**3. Contextual Confounder Rejection:**\n| Confounder | Sensor Signal | Rejection Rule |\n|------------|---------------|----------------|\n| Exercise | HR↑ HRV↓ EDA↑ | Pause scoring if accelerometer > 3 METs |\n| Caffeine | EDA↑ HR↑ | Morning window exclusion if logged |\n| Alcohol | HRV↓ Sleep↓ | Night-after flag, not risk elevation |\n| Fever/Illness | Skin Temp↑ HR↑ | SpO2 < 95% or temp > 38°C → medical mode |\n| Ambient Heat | EDA↑ | Skin temp + weather API correlation |\n\n**4. Human-in-the-Loop Confirmation:**\n- High-risk sensor prediction triggers **brief EMA check-in** (2-3 questions)\n- If EMA contradicts sensor, downgrade risk\n- If EMA confirms, escalate to clinician alert","x":1570,"y":-780,"width":450,"height":1060},
		{"id":"math-detail","type":"text","text":"## 🔢 Mathematical Model Specifications\n\n**1. EDA Decomposition (Tonic / Phasic):**\n```\nEDA_raw(t) = EDA_tonic(t) + EDA_phasic(t) + noise\nEDA_tonic = moving_average(EDA_raw, 60s)\nEDA_phasic = EDA_raw - EDA_tonic\nPhasic_peaks = find_peaks(EDA_phasic, height=0.01μS, distance=2s)\n```\n\n**2. Sleep Onset Time Variance:**\n```\nSleep_onset_variance = std(sleep_onset_times[-7:])\nRisk_flag = Sleep_onset_variance > 90 minutes\n```\n\n**3. HRV Reactivity Score:**\n```\nBaseline_RMSSD = mean(sleep_RMSSD[-7:])\nStress_RMSSD = min(RMSSD during EDA spike + HR surge window)\nReactivity = (Baseline_RMSSD - Stress_RMSSD) / Baseline_RMSSD\nRecovery_tau = time to return to 90% of baseline\n```\n\n**4. Multi-Modal Risk Score (with temporal stability):\n```\nR_daily = sigmoid(Σ w_i · f_i)\nR_stable = mean(R_daily[-3:])  // 3-day stability requirement\nAlert = R_stable > threshold AND EMA_confirms\n```\n\n**5. False Positive Penalty:**\n```\nif confounder_detected(exercise, alcohol, fever):\n    weight_sensor *= 0.3  // reduce sensor weight\n    require_EMA = True    // force human confirmation\n```","x":1575,"y":1820,"width":450,"height":1130},
		{"id":"roadmap-main","type":"text","text":"# ✅ Implementation Roadmap\n## From Research to Production-Grade Detection System\n\n### Phase 1: Signal Validation (Months 1-3)\n- Validate Samsung GW8 EDA vs. Empatica E4 gold standard\n- Validate sleep staging vs. polysomnography\n- Establish personal baseline collection protocol (14 days)\n\n### Phase 2: Feature Engineering (Months 3-6)\n- Implement tonic/phasic EDA decomposition\n- Build sleep-onset variance calculator (7-day rolling SD)\n- Develop HRV reactivity pipeline (stress event detection → ΔRMSSD)\n- Confounder rejection module (exercise, caffeine, illness)\n\n### Phase 3: Model Development (Months 6-9)\n- Train multimodal fusion model (clinical + behavioral + sensor)\n- Implement stability threshold for temporal consistency\n- Calibrate thresholds: inpatient (sens 80%) vs. outpatient (spec 95%)\n- AUC-ROC target: >0.85 (clinical + GM multimodal achieved 0.88)\n\n### Phase 4: Safety & Ethics (Months 9-12)\n- FDA 510(k) or De Novo pathway for Software as Medical Device (SaMD)\n- Liability framework: model predictions + clinical judgment, never replacement\n- Crisis protocol integration: 988 hotline, geolocation-based services\n- User consent: explicit opt-in for suicide risk monitoring\n\n### Phase 5: Deployment & Monitoring (Month 12+)\n- Rollout to high-risk populations first (bipolar, prior attempters)\n- Continuous model retraining with federated learning\n- Alert fatigue monitoring: track clinician override rates\n- Outcome tracking: reduction in suicide attempts vs. control group","x":2420,"y":670,"width":500,"height":1280},
		{"id":"hrv-main","type":"text","text":"## 💓 Heart Rate Variability (HRV)\n\n**Primary Metrics from Wearables:**\n- **RMSSD** — parasympathetic tone (most reliable on-wrist)\n- **HF-HRV** — vagal regulation of emotion\n- **LF/HF ratio** — sympathovagal balance (*higher error on PPG*)\n\n**Key Research Findings:**\n- **Low RMSSD** associated with moderate-to-high suicide risk (p=0.019) even in symptomatic patients\n- **Low HF-HRV** predicts suicidal ideation independent of depression/anxiety levels — transdiagnostic\n- **HRV Reactivity** (drop during stress vs. baseline) is STRONGER predictor than resting baseline alone\n- **Anger increase** during stress test negatively correlated with HF-HRV in attempters\n\n**Samsung Watch Accuracy:**\n- Sleep: HR r=0.94, RMSSD r=0.78, HF r=0.78\n- Awake: HR r=0.68, RMSSD r=0.25 (noisy during movement)\n- **Recommendation: Use sleep-time HRV for clinical-grade baselines**","x":280,"y":-600,"width":420,"height":760},
		{"id":"central-hub","type":"text","text":"# ⌚ Wearable Suicide Risk Detection\n## Passive, Continuous, Multi-Modal Biomarker System\n\n*A research-backed knowledge base on leveraging consumer wearables (Samsung Galaxy Watch, Google Pixel Watch) to detect suicidal ideation and self-harm risk through physiological biomarkers, mathematical fusion models, and false-positive reduction strategies.*","x":-460,"y":-1640,"width":520,"height":300},
		{"id":"fp-paper-2","type":"link","url":"https://pmc.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/articles/PMC11655152/","x":2270,"y":-625,"width":400,"height":400},
		{"id":"fp-paper-1","type":"link","url":"https://backend.orbit.dtu.dk/ws/files/335722054/document.pdf","x":1440,"y":550,"width":400,"height":400},
		{"id":"fp-threshold","type":"text","text":"### ⚖️ Threshold Calibration by Setting\n\n**Inpatient (High Sensitivity):**\n- Threshold: Lower (sensitivity ~80%)\n- Accept higher FPR because clinical staff already monitoring\n- 24/7 watch data + frequent check-ins\n\n**Outpatient / Community (High Specificity):**\n- Threshold: Higher (specificity ~95%)\n- Minimize alert fatigue — only flag clear patterns\n- Weekly clinician review of flagged cases\n\n**Kaiser Permanente Finding:**\nThe degree to which suicide risk models add to clinical workloads depends heavily on the risk threshold selected AND the response protocol. Without a defined workflow, even accurate models create burden.\n\n**Suggested 7-Day Window Protocol:**\n1. Day 1-2: Sensor anomaly detected → internal risk score rises\n2. Day 3: Risk persists → gentle EMA prompt ('How are you feeling?')\n3. Day 4-5: EMA + sensor both elevated → push notification to user + trusted contact\n4. Day 6-7: No improvement → clinician dashboard alert + outreach","x":1920,"y":670,"width":450,"height":750},
		{"id":"fp-jmir","type":"link","url":"https://formative.jmir.org/2022/3/e30946/","x":2270,"y":-150,"width":400,"height":400},
		{"id":"sensor-paper-samsung","type":"link","url":"https://pmc.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/articles/PMC9731465/","x":-2760,"y":-220,"width":960,"height":620}
	],
